England's Stuart Broad bowls during the first day of the test match between England and New Zealand at Lord's cricket ground in London, Thursday, June 2, 2022. (AP Photo/Kirsty Wigglesworth)England's Stuart Broad bowls during the first day of the test match between England and New Zealand at Lord's cricket ground in London, Thursday, June 2, 2022. (AP Photo/Kirsty Wigglesworth)LONDON (AP) — England’s test cricket team launched its new era on Thursday by losing the toss against New Zealand at Lord’s.New Zealand skipper Kane Williamson chose to bat first in the opening match of a three-test series. Ben Stokes, England’s recently appointed captain, said he would also have batted first.New Zealand, the reigning world test champion, is taking on an opponent now coached by Brendon McCullum, one of the Black Caps’ great players.Matthew Potts, a 23-year-old pacer, is making his international debut in any format for England. James Anderson, 39, and Stuart Broad, 35 — the most prolific wicket-takers in English test history — were selected in England’s lineup announced Wednesday after being dropped for the recent tour of the West Indies.Left-arm spinner Ajaz Patel, who is one of only three players to have taken 10 wickets in a test innings, was included in the New Zealand team on Thursday. Pacer Trent Boult also starts, despite only arriving in London on Monday.New Zealand beat England when the teams last met in a test series in England last year, prior to New Zealand’s win over India in the final of the inaugural World Test Championship. ADVERTISEMENTEngland is on a run of just one win in its last 17 tests.CricketPotts making debut as England recalls Anderson, Broad vs. NZAustralia coach out with COVID for start of Sri Lanka tourEngland must excite to attract stayaway fans, says BroadPCB shifts ODI series against West Indies to Multan___England: Alex Lees, Zak Crawley, Ollie Pope, Joe Root, Jonny Bairstow, Ben Stokes (captain), Ben Foakes, Matthew Potts, Jack Leach, Stuart Broad, James Anderson.New Zealand: Tom Latham, Will Young, Kane Williamson (captain), Devon Conway, Daryl Mitchell, Tom Blundell, Colin de Grandhomme, Kyle Jamieson, Tim Southee, Ajaz Patel, Trent Boult.___More AP cricket: https://apnews.com/hub/cricket and https://twitter.com/AP_Sports